&lt;h3 id=&#34;Ligatures&#34;&gt;Ligatures&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most letters follow a consistent script, a form of insular script, but a close reader may notice some aberrant symbols. The scribe, to save space, will often combine two letters into one glyph in a process called “ligature”. A table of some of these occurrences is presented:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
&lt;thead&gt;
